        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:12PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of Winifred, or 36 miles north of Lewistown, moving north
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Fergus, southwestern Blaine and southeastern Chouteau Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
